review_blob:
GJS spared no expense when producing this brewing gem! An aroma of blood and steel overwhelm the senses... The color is an unsettling orange (the taste, aroma and color are probably imparted by rusty fermenting tanks)... This has to be the worst cheap beer I have ever drank.  Stick to 40s of malt liqour, you get more bang for the buck AND taste much better.

Furthermore what is with the name?!  Pennsylvania has many quality craft breweries!!! this beer defiles our state and its brewing tradition!
